/* FONT LOADING TEMPLATE                                        */
/* ============================================================ */
/* 
   Copy this file to fonts-{client}.css and customize for your client.
   
   Examples:
   - cp css/fonts.css.template css/fonts-sqmhc.css
   - cp css/fonts.css.template css/fonts-fcp.css
   
   Then uncomment and edit the section(s) you need.

   Remote loading of fonts is the easiest method to set up for
   this styleguide app, so do that with Google/Adobe Fonts if possible.
   
   A site using custom fonts will need to have the fonts in .woff2
   format and dropped into fonts (TTF fonts are usually not licensed
   for web distribution). 
   
   Make sure you drop them in a fonts subfolder 
   named after your project, and reference them properly in
   the css/fonts-*.css file. Example:

   font-family: 'urbanedemi_bold';
   src: url('../fonts/fcp/Urbane-DemiBold.woff2') format('woff2');
*/

